apply_filters('piklist_empty_post_title', $data['post_title'], $post_array); Let’s you programmatically set the post title when adding a new post (post type).
Example:
// Set the Post Title to &quot;Order #&quot; plus post ID: function set_post_title_to_order_number($data, $post_array) { if ($post_array['post_type'] == 'MY-POST-TYPE') { return 'Order #' . $post_array['ID']; } else { return $data; } } add_filter('piklist_empty_post_title', 'set_post_title_to_order_number', 10, 2);  IMPORTANT: This filter works best when there is no title field for posts. To disable the title field, do not pass &ldquo;title&rdquo; to the supports parameter when registering a post type.
